article.headline: Hofstra 81, Towson 67
article.story: EDS: Hofstra 81, Towson 67; SUBS 2nd graf to CORRECT Hofstra's streak to three of four; SUBS 3rd graf to CORRECT Hairston's first name; SUBS 5th graf to CORRECT score to 74-61;. HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Antoine Agudio scored 15 of his 27 points in the second half to lead Hofstra to an 81-67 victory over Towson on Wednesday night. Charles Jenkins added 17 points for the Pride (10-16, 7-9 Colonial Athletic Association), who have won three of four. Josh Thornton scored 21 points to lead the Tigers (10-16, 6-10), who trailed 38-37 at halftime but lost their 11th straight road league game. C.C. Williams added 15 points and seven assists and Junior Hairston had 12 points. Hairston's three-point play gave the Tigers their last lead of the game, 55-53 at 9:43. Agudio had a 3-pointer to start a 21-6 run that put Hofstra on top 74-61 at 4:33. Jenkins connected on one of two foul shots to close out the rally.
